Usage: $$s [options] <ncl_filename>.
Compile NCL files to a NCD or NCM.
Options:
-bi -- Assume all IOs are bonded.
-Dname[=value] -- cpp options. See cpp man page.
-drc -- Do not do any DRC checks.
-drcwarn -- Suppress all DRC warnings. Only report DRC errors.
-drcrt -- Do not do DRC routing checks.
-drcpl -- Do not do DRC placement checks.
-drcsanity -- Do not do DRC "design sanity" checks. These
checks find errors caused by incorrect NCLs
and/or errors in routing specifications in your
NCL.
-drcnamechk -- Do not do DRC "name check" checks. These
checks find potential naming conflicts between
signals and comps which would cause problems
with back end tools.
-I -- cpp options. See cpp man page.
-m -- Only write the macro definitions as NCM
files.
-mp <macroDir> -- Directory path to search for macros.
To specify one or more directories multiple -mp
maybe used.
-ns -- Instead of using the system place to find
system macros use the macro path.
-o <fileName> -- Output file name. If not specified then the
design name with extension ".ncd" will be used.
-P -- Process the NCL using cpp before compilation.
-pl -- Ignore placement specification in the NCL.
-r -- Ignore routing specification in the NCL.
-Uname -- cpp options. See cpp man page.
-undef -- cpp options. See cpp man page.
-v -- Verbose option! For debugging.
Comments:
In general use of options to disable DRC is not advisable. Designs
generated without DRC check may have errors which could cause
unexpected results in the down stream tools.
